# Git commit and push

When you complete a task that modifies project files (not only advice or read-only exploration), **commit the changes with a clear message and push to `origin`** on the current branch (usually `main`), unless the user explicitly asks not to use git or there is no remote.

If there is nothing new to commit, say so briefly.
